LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 210
BY LOCAL GOVERNMENT COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO POWERS AND DUTIES OF BOARDS OF COMMISSIONERS; AMENDING SECTION
3 31-819, IDAHO CODE, TO REVISE PROVISIONS REGARDING PUBLICATION OF PRO-
4 CEEDINGS; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
5 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
6 SECTION 1. That Section 31-819, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
7 amended to read as follows:
8 31-819. PUBLICATION OF PROCEEDINGS. (1) To The board of county commis-
9 sioners shall cause to be published monthly such statement as will clearly
10 give notice to the public of all its acts and proceedings, and, shall in-
11 clude including a brief financial summary indicating the total amount spent
12 from each county fund during the month. A more detailed report of expendi-
13 tures may be published if deemed necessary by the board. Monthly publica-
14 tion of acts and proceedings shall not be required for any county that main-
15 tains a publicly accessible website on which agendas and minutes of the meet-
16 ings of the board of county commissioners are posted. Monthly publication of
17 a financial summary indicating the total amount spent from each fund during
18 the month shall be required and shall include the website link for accessing
19 agendas and meeting minutes.
20 (2) Annually, a full financial report shall be prepared and available
21 for public inspection which that shows for each fund the sources of income,
22 expenditures during the year, current fund balances, and other financial in-
23 formation as determined by the board. Within thirty (30) days of the annual
24 audit's preparation as provided in section 31-1701, Idaho Code, the board
25 shall cause to be published a summary of the balance sheet and a summary of
26 the statement of revenues and expenditures. Such statements as well as all
27 other public notices of proceedings of, or to be had before the board, not
28 otherwise specially provided for, must be published in accordance with the
29 requirements of chapter 1, title 60, Idaho Code.
30 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
31 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
32 July 1, 2025.

